  "prompt": "What is the English word for the Tagalog word \u201ckinikilig\u201d?",
  "response": "The English word that most closely captures the Tagalog word \"kinikilig\" is \"giddy.\" \"Kinikilig\" refers to the feeling of excitement or butterflies in the stomach often associated with romantic situations or infatuation. However, it is important to note that the exact nuance and cultural context may not be fully captured by the single English word \"giddy.\"",
